@DATABASE "Virus Info Base"
@NODE MAIN "Turk v1.3"

     Name         : Turk Virus v1.3

     Aliases      : No Aliases

     Type/Size    : Boot/1024

     Clones       : No Clones 

     Symptoms     : No Symptoms

     Discovered   : 03-04-91

     Way to infect: Boot infection

     Rating       : Dangerous

     Kickstarts   : 1.2/1.3/2.0 (not sure!)

     Damage       : Overwrites boot + Formats Disk.

     Removal      : Install boot.

     Comments     : The  Turk virus v 1.3 is a dangerous virus. If you are
                    are  booting  with it 5.th times it formats your disks
                    and shows an alert (see below).


                    To stay resident the virus copies itself to $7F000 and
                    changes  the  CoolCapture.  To  infect other disks the
                    virus  uses  the  DoIO()-vector from the exec.library.
                    After  the 10.th infection the virus formats your disk
                    and show the following alert:


                    "Amiga Failure... Cause: TURK VIRUS Version 1.3"


                    Click  on  this  gadget  to  see  a @{" Demo " SYSTEM V-IFF:Turk} of the Turk
                    virus. Push left mouse button to return.


                    I`m  not sure if the virus works with Kick2.0 machines
                    or  higher  properly,  because  it  writes  values  to
                    addresses  like  $120  or  300. Further more the virus
                    writes  "TURK"  at  $60  this can cause GURUS (also on
                    Kick 1.2/1.3 Machines!).


                    The  above  written Alert-Text is crypted so you can`t
                    read it in the Bootblock.

A.D 08-94

@ENDNODE
